RUSTENBURG - Authorities in Rustenburg are providing food and accommodation to those displaced by floods.They are also urging residents to take all necessary precautions during the wet weather.The heavy rain has left at least two people dead.UPDATE: Three die in flooding in North West provinceTwenty-year-old Bonolo Tshelane was swept away by flood waters. Family and friends are still struggling to come to terms with her death.Emergency services say they've had their hands full since the flooding started.Thapelo Matebesi from the Rustenburg Municipality said, "It was hectic. I must say this is the third day now that the municipality has been wrestling with this dire, desperate situation."IN PICTURES: Rain and flooding across SA eNCA